101
00:07:07,438 --> 00:07:09,407
I'm worried about you.

102
00:07:09,431 --> 00:07:10,417
Really?

103
00:07:10,441 --> 00:07:11,429
Something's different, John.

104
00:07:11,453 --> 00:07:15,417
The party, the way you tried to take on that masked thief

105
00:07:15,441 --> 00:07:17,431
even the way you talk.. It isn't you.

106
00:07:17,455 --> 00:07:19,417
What's the matter, Brucie?

107
00:07:19,441 --> 00:07:21,422
Scared of a little social competition?

108
00:07:21,446 --> 00:07:23,434
People change, I apologize if I no longer fit

109
00:07:23,458 --> 00:07:26,442
into some comfortable role you've once defined for me.

110
00:07:26,466 --> 00:07:29,429
I didn't mean to upset you.

111
00:07:29,453 --> 00:07:30,461
I'm sorry.

112
00:07:32,454 --> 00:07:33,443
It's fine.

113
00:07:33,467 --> 00:07:36,479
Truth is, I have been a little all over the place lately.

114
00:07:38,458 --> 00:07:39,470
Oh, my.

115
00:07:54,485 --> 00:07:56,458
Okay, still confused.

116
00:07:56,482 --> 00:07:58,458
Marlowe's company's been conducting experiments

117
00:07:58,482 --> 00:07:59,923
in quantum theory for the government.

118
00:08:00,481 --> 00:08:02,461
Which explains why he's radioactive

119
00:08:02,485 --> 00:08:04,478
but what's the deal with him not stealing stuff?

120
00:08:04,502 --> 00:08:06,503
There's always an explanation.

121
00:08:08,491 --> 00:08:10,472
'The readings point to two radiation hot-spots'

122
00:08:10,496 --> 00:08:11,479
in the building.

123
00:08:11,503 --> 00:08:13,478
I'll take this one. You track the other.

124
00:08:13,502 --> 00:08:15,494
- And be care... - Please don't say it.

125
00:08:15,518 --> 00:08:17,493
Fine. Go.

126
00:08:17,517 --> 00:08:19,501
Swish swish

127
00:08:36,536 --> 00:08:38,524
beep beep.

128
00:08:50,546 --> 00:08:54,548
The sign said "Authorized personnel only," Batman.

129
00:09:02,557 --> 00:09:04,525
So what happens now, Marlowe?

130
00:09:04,549 --> 00:09:06,525
You teleport away again?

131
00:09:06,549 --> 00:09:09,530
Is that what I've been doing?

132
00:09:09,554 --> 00:09:12,530
No, there's a much simpler explanation

133
00:09:12,554 --> 00:09:14,557
and it's right behind you.

134
00:09:18,560 --> 00:09:21,547
Then your quantum technology isn't behind this.

135
00:09:21,571 --> 00:09:22,551
That means all you had

136
00:09:22,575 --> 00:09:24,586
was an accomplice in the same costume.

137
00:09:25,565 --> 00:09:26,574
Getting warmer.

138
00:09:31,588 --> 00:09:35,593
Beep whoosh

139
00:09:47,605 --> 00:09:48,609
ding.

140
00:09:51,594 --> 00:09:52,606
Going up?

141
00:09:55,613 --> 00:09:56,617
Huh.

142
00:10:08,610 --> 00:10:09,621
Enjoying the ride?

143
00:10:10,616 --> 00:10:11,631
Beats the company.

144
00:10:18,636 --> 00:10:21,604
Ding 'Penthouse level.'

145
00:10:21,628 --> 00:10:23,621
Nefarious plots, brilliant schemes

146
00:10:23,645 --> 00:10:25,639
doomed heroes.

147
00:10:29,636 --> 00:10:30,648
Have a nice evening.

148
00:10:32,641 --> 00:10:34,615
You've been expected.

149
00:10:34,639 --> 00:10:38,621
Welcome, Batman. We've been waiting for you.

150
00:10:38,645 --> 00:10:40,631
Allow me to introduce myself.

151
00:10:40,655 --> 00:10:43,659
I am the Everywhere Man.

152
00:10:47,669 --> 00:10:49,640
'Batman's in custody'

153
00:10:49,664 --> 00:10:51,644
'but his partner may already be in the building.'

154
00:10:51,668 --> 00:10:54,642
- What's our priority? - Securing the prisoner.

155
00:10:54,666 --> 00:10:55,653
We might need more men.

156
00:10:55,677 --> 00:10:57,637
Then we'll make more.

157
00:10:57,661 --> 00:10:58,672
Beep.

158
00:11:01,684 --> 00:11:04,687
Okay, so my broom theory was way off.

159
00:11:05,666 --> 00:11:07,670
Time to bust out Batman.

160
00:11:10,672 --> 00:11:12,660
It was the quantum-field research, of course.

161
00:11:12,684 --> 00:11:14,661
It lead to the creation of the Quantex.

162
00:11:14,685 --> 00:11:18,679
With it, I can charge my body's quantum particles..

163
00:11:20,694 --> 00:11:22,665
And replicate another me.

164
00:11:22,689 --> 00:11:24,671
My energy duplicates can split at will

165
00:11:24,695 --> 00:11:27,708
but with the Quantex, I can also recall them at will..

166
00:11:30,694 --> 00:11:31,685
Even from a distance.

167
00:11:31,709 --> 00:11:33,716
Which is how you escaped from the broom closet.

168
00:11:34,695 --> 00:11:36,719
Sleight of hand, I know, yet effective.

169
00:11:37,698 --> 00:11:40,713
Still, that's only the tip of the Quantex iceberg.

170
00:11:41,712 --> 00:11:42,713
Beep.

171
00:11:45,705 --> 00:11:47,685
Please, sit down.

172
00:11:47,709 --> 00:11:48,699
I'll stand.

173
00:11:48,723 --> 00:11:51,702
Your device made quantum copies of the art at the museum.

174
00:11:51,726 --> 00:11:55,695
Leaving me free to steal the originals for my collection.

175
00:11:55,719 --> 00:11:58,722
You mean for John Marlowe's collection.

176
00:12:15,744 --> 00:12:18,716
- The prisoner? - Secure inside.

177
00:12:18,740 --> 00:12:20,732
'They must have Batman in there.'

178
00:12:20,756 --> 00:12:21,760
'Uh-oh.'

179
00:12:26,759 --> 00:12:27,767
clang

180
00:12:31,756 --> 00:12:32,757
thwack

181
00:12:36,758 --> 00:12:37,764
beep

182
00:12:38,765 --> 00:12:39,768
whack.

183
00:12:41,769 --> 00:12:42,746
Unh..

184
00:12:42,770 --> 00:12:44,785
Hold on, Batman. Almost there.

185
00:12:56,792 --> 00:12:57,796
Hmm?

186
00:12:59,793 --> 00:13:01,788
You're not Batman.

187
00:13:04,784 --> 00:13:05,780
'You're not John Marlowe.'

188
00:13:05,804 --> 00:13:07,777
You're just another counterfeit.

189
00:13:07,801 --> 00:13:09,784
You're hot with the same quantum radiation signature

190
00:13:09,808 --> 00:13:12,772
we found on the copies at the museum.

191
00:13:12,796 --> 00:13:14,518
And there was nothing in his past to suggest

192
00:13:14,795 --> 00:13:16,795
the real John Marlowe would commit these crimes.

193
00:13:16,819 --> 00:13:18,788
Very good, Batman.

194
00:13:18,812 --> 00:13:20,779
I was copy number one.

195
00:13:20,803 --> 00:13:23,788
Sometimes it takes an upgrade to get things right.

196
00:13:23,812 --> 00:13:25,793
Johnny may be a brilliant scientist

197
00:13:25,817 --> 00:13:26,828
but he's also a fool.

198
00:13:27,807 --> 00:13:29,329
He kept me around to be his lab partner

199
00:13:29,809 --> 00:13:30,805
but keep a duplicate around long enough

200
00:13:30,829 --> 00:13:32,825
and you know what you get?

201
00:13:33,834 --> 00:13:35,798
Free will.

202
00:13:35,822 --> 00:13:37,808
Johnny and I both loved our art collection

203
00:13:37,832 --> 00:13:38,993
'but he wasn't willing to do'

204
00:13:39,819 --> 00:13:41,799
what was necessary to add to it.

205
00:13:41,823 --> 00:13:42,805
I was.

206
00:13:42,829 --> 00:13:43,815
Enough with the art collection.

207
00:13:43,839 --> 00:13:45,848
All this power, and we're only stealing paintings.

208
00:13:46,827 --> 00:13:47,813
Excuse me?

209
00:13:47,837 --> 00:13:48,820
Who cares about art?

210
00:13:48,844 --> 00:13:50,825
We could use the Quantex to conquer the world.

211
00:13:50,849 --> 00:13:52,831
Like a bad photocopy

212
00:13:52,855 --> 00:13:55,832
each duplicate is just a little darker than the last.

213
00:13:55,856 --> 00:13:56,835
Shut up!

214
00:13:56,859 --> 00:13:59,831
Don't tell him to shut up. Shut him up.

215
00:13:59,855 --> 00:14:02,829
Look, if you can't handle things, I will.

216
00:14:02,853 --> 00:14:06,827
Whoosh See? Free will.

217
00:14:06,851 --> 00:14:08,828
But I know how to deal with it.

218
00:14:08,852 --> 00:14:09,846
And Johnny didn't.

219
00:14:09,870 --> 00:14:11,845
No, he didn't.

220
00:14:11,869 --> 00:14:13,852
So you got rid of him.

221
00:14:13,876 --> 00:14:15,877
I never get rid of anything.

222
00:14:16,856 --> 00:14:18,842
I'm a collector, Batman.

223
00:14:18,866 --> 00:14:21,884
And you keep your collection close at hand.

224
00:14:22,863 --> 00:14:25,882
John Marlowe's in this building, which is all I wanted to know.

225
00:14:26,884 --> 00:14:27,887
Boom.

226
00:14:35,891 --> 00:14:37,868
Attention, Everywhere Man

227
00:14:37,892 --> 00:14:39,875
'the Batman is loose in our building.'

228
00:14:39,899 --> 00:14:43,888
'You know the drill. Divide and conquer.'

229
00:14:44,886 --> 00:14:47,886
whoosh whoosh whoosh 'Fill the corridors.'

