248
00:16:24,006 --> 00:16:27,009
Yeah, but if I'm not just one more?

249
00:16:27,988 --> 00:16:29,983
'What are you doing with my prototype?'

250
00:16:30,007 --> 00:16:31,012
beep.

251
00:16:36,002 --> 00:16:37,018
Check out <i>my army.</i>

252
00:16:51,019 --> 00:16:53,014
Boom boom boom.

253
00:16:56,026 --> 00:16:58,002
How's it going, Batman?

254
00:16:58,026 --> 00:17:01,024
Better, now that you're here, partners.

255
00:17:06,033 --> 00:17:08,049
Well, if it isn't old Johnny boy.

256
00:17:09,028 --> 00:17:11,019
I knew I should have eliminated you.

257
00:17:11,043 --> 00:17:13,024
'I always was too sentimental.'

258
00:17:13,048 --> 00:17:15,015
True.

259
00:17:15,039 --> 00:17:17,020
You even saved the Quantex prototype.

260
00:17:17,044 --> 00:17:19,017
That's going to be your downfall.

261
00:17:19,041 --> 00:17:21,037
There's a reason a prototype's only a prototype.

262
00:17:21,061 --> 00:17:24,058
'Sometimes it takes an upgrade to get things right.'

263
